{
  "stem": "20089.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But at the time, I had the criticism of the black market, and that they weren't clean.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They weren't-- they weren't as hygienic as the-- as the Americans are.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They weren't anal in their-- [LAUGHS] in their habits of cleanliness.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I think it's-- in retrospect, it's very difficult to-- for one madrich to be able to really keep the place in-- in-- in perfect condition.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I think I should mention this now about the cupboards in the-- in the dormitories and in-- and in-- with the families.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I think at the beginning of '47, the Americans were rather interested in what had happened in the camps.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And a group of American congressmen were visiting the displaced persons camp.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I got word from Miss Richman that I must go around through to all the dormitories and to clean-- clean them up, to make sure that the place was clean, because Americans would only go back and-- and say, we can take these people as immigrants on condition things were very good.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There was a very, very low-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] not-- a very low ratio, I think it is, or-- of Polish immigrants who could go to America.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The best ratio was the German.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So a lot of Poles got German papers and could go to Poland quite-- to America quite easily.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When it came to the Polish immigrants, it was rather difficult.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the American congressmen were coming out to have a look at the camps-- the Lithuanian camp-- the camps with the Lithuanians and the Polish survivors or the Polish immigrants were-- Polish people who wanted to immigrate were.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And so one of the duties that I had was to make sure that everything was spick and span and clean.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
